  "text": "Illes-Seifert and Paech [CITATION_1] investigate the role of communication, documentation and experience during system testing. They found that ''most communication during the testing process occurs with the requirements engineer and the project manager followed by the developer.'' This is a type of pattern we had expected to be able to find in our interview data, but we cannot confirm or reject their finding. However, we note that communication patterns like this one could be of importance to the practice of software testing.",
